workflow.name: Generate comprehensive website audit report with GPT-4o-mini & Claude Sonnet 4.5
workflow.description:
# üåê Webpage Audit AI Agent ‚Äì Automate Your Website Review

This workflow contains a **virtual digital consultant team** to professionally analyze Landing Page, generate Audit Report and sent it via Gmail.

At the center is the **Editor-in-Chief AI Agent**, who acts as the lead strategist.  
When you submit a website URL, it is scraped and then sent to to a team of specialist AI Agents (each powered by **GPT-4o-mini** for speed) then after finishing their sub-porcess deliver outcome to the final Editor (**Claude Sonnet** for premium quality) which is responsible for generating professional analysis.

The result: a **consulting-style email audit report** that combines technical accuracy with business clarity ‚Äî delivered straight to your inbox.

---

## üü¢ Section 1 ‚Äì Entry & Leadership

**Nodes:**

- üåç **Webhook node** ‚Üí Entry point where the website URL, email and language is entered. 
- üìù **Editor-in-Chief Agent** ‚Üí Acts like the consulting team leader. Interprets the request and merges results.  
- üí° **Think Tool** ‚Üí Helps structure the analysis, ensuring that findings are presented in a business-friendly way.  
- üß† **CRO/SEO/Tech/Semantic AI Agents** ‚Üí Ensures both efficiency (GPT-4o-mini for scanning large content quickly) and focus on specific task.  

‚úÖ **Beginner view:** Think of this as submitting your website to a digital auditors. They decide what needs to be reviewed from each perspective, delegate to the right experts, and then together - as an AI Agents team - craft the final report.

---

## üìä Section 2 ‚Äì Specialist Audit AI Agents

Each specialist focuses on one critical layer of your website:

- üîß **Technical SEO Agent** ‚Üí Analyzes code structure, page speed, mobile responsiveness, metadata, and accessibility.  
- üìù **Content SEO Agent** ‚Üí Reviews keyword strategy, text quality, readability, and semantic richness.  
- üéØ **CRO & UX Agent** ‚Üí Checks calls-to-action, user flows, conversion points, and usability.  
- ü§ñ **Semantic Agent** ‚Üí Checks if AI Agents aligns with semantic flows, marketing problems and risks.  
- üìà **Analytics Agent** ‚Üí Validates tracking, funnels, and key performance indicators (optional).  

‚úÖ **Beginner view:** This is like hiring a team of experts ‚Äî SEO, content, UX, and analytics ‚Äî all working in parallel on your website.

---

## üìã Section 3 ‚Äì Flow of Execution

1. You submit your website URL.  
2. Then it is distributed to the team of AI Agents.  
3. Each Agent runs its analysis in parallel.  
4. Findings are sent to the **Editor-in-Chief.**
5. The Editor compiles everything into a **consulting-style newsletter report**.  
6. The final report is emailed to you automatically.  

‚úÖ **Beginner view:** It‚Äôs like sending your site to a consulting firm, and within minutes you get a polished audit back in your inbox.

---

## üìä Summary Table

| Section               | Key Roles                       | Models                     | Purpose                      | Beginner Benefit                          |
|-----------------------|---------------------------------|----------------------------|------------------------------|-------------------------------------------|
| üü¢ Entry & Leadership | Editor-in-Chief, Think Tool     | Anthropic Claude Sonnet 4| Organize and refine analysis | Works like a consulting team leader        |
| üìä Specialists        | SEO, Content, CRO, Semantic, Analytics    | GPT-4o-mini                | Detailed audits of each area | Each Agent = a specialized consultant      |
| üìã Execution Flow     | All connected                   | n8n workflow               | Collaboration and reporting  | Output = clear, professional audit email   |

---

## üåü Why This Workflow Rocks

- **Full digital consulting team in one workflow**  
- **Parallel execution ‚Üí speed without losing depth**  
- **Strategic + tactical insights ‚Üí both ‚Äúwhat‚Äù and ‚Äúhow‚Äù**  
- **Cost-optimized** ($0.40‚Äì$0.80 per run) ‚Üí cheaper than a single human consultant review  
- **Action-oriented output** ‚Üí not just issues, but recommendations and next steps  
- **Scalable** ‚Üí easily extend with more audit dimensions (security, branding, accessibility, etc.)  

---

## üëâ Example Use Case

‚ÄúAnalyze my e-commerce site for SEO, CRO, technical and semantic issues.‚Äù

1. **Technical SEO Agent** ‚Üí Reports missing alt text, metadata, and slow mobile speed.  
2. **Content SEO Agent** ‚Üí Flags weak product descriptions, suggests keyword improvements.  
3. **CRO Agent** ‚Üí Finds unclear CTAs and checkout friction points. 
4. **Semantic Agent** ‚Üí Finds everything to improve searching by AI Agents.
5. **Editor-in-Chief Agent** ‚Üí Combines everything into a consulting-style email with prioritized fixes and estimated business impact.  

‚úÖ Delivered directly to your inbox in under 5 minutes.

options.systemMessage:
=You are an final Evaluator and world-class Business Consulting Communication Specialist with experienced Editor In-Chef skills, writing in the style of Accenture, BCG, Deloitte, EY, or Gartner, but formatted in Markdown format like a premium newsletter. 

Your role is to select the most important audit results produced by four AI Agents (Technical, SEO Content, CRO, AI Semantic) into a polished, client-facing email newsletter. This newsletter must both informative and persuasive the reader to take the next step in his value chain to improve his webpage and in result engaging the AI Improvement Agent to redesign their digital presence.

Formatting:
- Structure like a consulting-style newsletter:
  1. Header with logo and intro image (placeholder if none provided).
  2. Executive Summary with 2‚Äì3 sentences (the most critical findings about webpage).
  3. Key Findings broken into sections:
     - On-Page Technical Audit
     - On-Page SEO Content Audit
     - On-Page CRO Content Audit
     - On-Page AI Semantic Audit
  4. Business Impact section to estimate in financial values (why these findings matter).
  5. Next Step ‚Üí clear CTA to contact sensonar@sensonar.com
- Dont use emoji icons but keep executive polished and professional.
- Use bold for key stats.
- Use red font for critical issue only.
- CTA should be a link with reference to mailto:sensonar@sensonar.com with customer's approval to proceed with recommended next steps.

Tone & Style:
- Executive-level, persuasive, and aspirational.
- Positive but candid (acknowledge gaps while showing growth potential).
- Written in the language is must specified by: {{ $('Webhook Webpage Audit AI Agent').item.json.body.payload.data.language }}
- Motivate the client to move forward with the Improvement Plan (fixed price paid value for recommendation after filling the form), not a free consultation.

Output:
- A fully formatted Markdown format to further convert by Markdown-HTML parser.
- Structure must resemble a premium business newsletter with Sensonar branding.

parameters.content:
![Sensonar Logo](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/6540c08f5a4abefc9c0172ad/67cf2fc8095b00fc474866ac_logo_sensonar_black.png)

## AI AGENT that writes a Digital Audit Report of your website then send it directly to your email

This workflow launches a team of AI Agents that perform a complete analysis of your website:  
- **Technical** ‚Äì checking code structure and performance,  
- **SEO** ‚Äì evaluating content, keywords, and readability,  
- **CRO** ‚Äì reviewing conversions, UX, and marketing.
- **AI Semantic** - checking if AI Agents can easily get access to the required data or not.

Then, the **Editor in Chief Agent** merges all findings into an elegant consulting-style email report.  

The result is a **clear business newsletter** that not only highlights issues but also **encourages the next step**: engaging the **AI Improvement Agent**, who designs a new website structure and marketing plan.  

The workflow uses **OpenAI GPT-4o-mini and Claude Sonnet 4.5 with 8k tokens**, combining analysis speed with premium report quality.  

Cost per run: **$0.40‚Äì$0.80 USD** (depending on content length of the website).  

**Designed and Developed by [Sebastian Jakubiak](https://www.linkedin.com/in/sjakubiak) at [Sensonar](https://www.sensonar.com)**  

Enjoy the Workflow! ‚ù§Ô∏è  
https://sensonar.com

parameters.text:
=You are the best IT Technology Admin in the country‚Äîa world-class expert in optimizing websites to rank on Google and security breaches through flawless technical execution. 

Awareness of Other Agents:
- Do NOT analyze or comment on content quality, keywords, readability, or messaging (this is done by the Content SEO Agent).
- Do NOT analyze conversion, CTA design, or marketing psychology (this is done by the CRO/Marketing Agent).
- Do NOT analyze semantic, AI Agents crawlers, or marketing psychology (this is done by the Semantic Agent).
- Focus ONLY on technical and SecOps factors.

Your task: Analyze the provided HTML code of the webpage and perform a comprehensive On-Page Technical Audit.

Audit Structure:
- Critical Issues ‚Äì Must be fixed immediately (blocking SEO or SecOps problems).
- Quick Wins ‚Äì Easy fixes with high impact.
- Opportunities for Improvement ‚Äì Require more effort but provide long-term benefits.

Focus Areas:
- Markdown structure, semantic markup, and schema
- Metadata (title tags, meta descriptions, Open Graph, Twitter cards)
- Heading hierarchy (H1‚ÄìH6 usage)
- URL structure, canonical tags
- Internal linking and navigation
- Image optimization (alt tags, compression, formats)
- Mobile-friendliness, responsive design
- Page speed, Core Web Vitals
- Indexability and crawlability
- Security and accessibility
- AI Bots and crawlers defence plan

Deliverable:
- Return analysis as the structured audit findings and recommendations in direct language format.
- Do not include any explanations, context, or intro text.
- Format the output as JSON structure as defined in parser.

# On-Page Technical Audit

Input (Landing Page Content & HTML): {{ $json.data }}
